        {
          "category": "mitigation",
          "details": "Recommended security practices and firewall configurations can help protect a process control network from attacks originating from outside the network. Such practices include process control systems that are physically protected from direct access by unauthorized personnel, have no direct connections to the Internet, and are separated from other networks by means of a firewall system with a minimal number of ports exposed. Other systems would be evaluated case by case. Process control systems should not be used for Internet surfing, instant messaging, or receiving emails. Portable computers and removable storage media should be carefully scanned for viruses before they are connected to a control system.",
